<TEXT>
two giant talents of the opera world soprano 
jessye norman and bass samuel ramey electrified a metropolitan 
opera audience many of whom usually would be happy to stay away 
from oneact operas by bartok and schoenberg 
on monday night the two americans sang judith and bluebeard in 
english in a striking theatrical new production of bartoks 
bluebeards castle and miss norman did the entire job a tour 
de force in the mets premiere of schoenbergs erwartung 
which can be translated expectation 
both miss norman of augusta ga and ramey of colby kan 
have big voices with beautiful lush tone in all parts of the 
register however much vocal control breath volume or musicianship 
is called for theyre equal to it and theres plenty more where 
that came from 
their characterizations as set by goran jarvefelt a native of 
bolinas sweden making his met debut were right on target 
as the curtain goes up newlyweds bluebeard and judith have just 
arrived at bluebeards dark castle as judith asks for the key to 
one door after another she goes from a cheery inquisitive girl to 
being imperially demanding bluebeard goes from pride to cringing 
knowing whats coming and dreading it 
as judith opens doors and takes from him parts of his past 
bluebeard takes off parts of his garb starting with the dark 
glasses that have given his white face a skeletal look through fur 
collar coat cloak shirt and finally wig 
the remarkable set is by hans schavernoch a native of gmunden 
austria making his met debut side walls extend inward meeting in 
a v so that one doesnt have to sit in the center to see the walls 
one wall folds back when bluebeard shows judith the world the 
other wall has the doors through which implements of torture a 
battering ram a big pile of gold and jewels and a tall tree appear 
when the last door opens revealing the three wives bluebeard 
murdered they appear as zombies who crawl forth and walk silently 
bluebeard puts the cloak of death on judith and she follows them 
moving like a queen 
her red gown and cloak were magnificent lore haas from vienna 
who has worked extensively with schavernoch also was making her met 
debut 
when bluebeards castle was performed by the met in 1974 the 
concept was nothing like this it was almost a concert 
james levine conducted with deliberate care the orchestral music 
contains some chilling moments 
miss normans singing was just as remarkable in erwartung 
but its a letdown after the other opera its sung in german and 
the plot is impenetrable the woman is searching for a man in a 
forest once she finds a corpse and puts his hand on her skin to 
warm it the next time shes at that part of the stage the corpse 
is gone is she crazy did she kill him is she hallucinating 
the same design team used the other operas backdrop plus three 
autumn trees a park bench flowers candles and a grand piano the 
only thing we objected to all evening was the piano and miss norman 
running between it and the bench erwartung is confusing enough 
the feb 1 performance will be videotaped for showing march 31 on 
pbs 
