<TEXT>
doctors have long recognized the power of 
female sex hormones to keep womens hearts healthy now theres 
evidence that abundant levels of testosterone may be good for mens 
hearts 
its attractive to think that being male is good for men and 
being female is good for women said dr elizabeth barrettconnor 
a physician at the university of california san diego 
estrogen the female hormone is believed to one of the key 
differences between the sexes that explains why women typically live 
seven to eight years longer than men 
barrettconnor presented evidence monday that men with high 
levels of testosterone the male hormone are in better shape than 
those with relatively low levels whether this means they are more 
likely to escape heart attacks is still unclear 
her work presented monday at a meeting of the american heart 
association is based on a followup of 5000 california residents 
who were first examined in 1972 
she found that men with high testosterone also have higher levels 
of high density lipoprotein or hdl the socalled good cholesterol 
that protects people from heart attacks they also have lower blood 
pressure and are less likely to be overweight 
in other words testosterone is good for men she said 
however despite these attributes that would seem to lower the 
risk of heart disease there was no clear evidence that the men with 
higher testosterone actually lived longer barrettconnor noted that 
the bodys levels of sex hormones fluctuate throughout the day and 
since her research was based on just one blood sample it might not 
have accurately identified differences between the mens hormone 
levels 
she also noted that even if testosterone turns out to be good for 
mens hearts she does not advocate taking extra doses of the 
hormone 
she said another major study has begun to see what effect 
estrogen pills have on womens risk of heart attacks after they go 
through menopause when their bodies natural production of the 
chemical drops sharply 
some of the women will take estrogen alone while others will get 
a combination of estrogen and progestin estrogen by itself can 
increase the risk of uterine cancer but while the estrogen and 
progestin combination eliminates this hazard some doctors fear that 
the extra progestin wipes out estrogens benefits for the heart 
among other research presented monday 
dr redford b williams jr of duke university said that anger 
not impatience is the key element of type a behavior that raises 
the risk of heart disease he said that those with a heart 
attackprone personality are more likely to get angry to become 
suspicious of other peoples motives and to show their hostility 
toward others 
according to dr wayne j katon of the university of washington 
panic attacks and depression are frequently mistaken for heart 
disease especially among young and middleaged women during panic 
attacks people may gasp for breath grow dizzy tremble feel chest 
pain and believe they are going to die 
strokes occur in two or three of every 100000 children dr 
dorothy m aram of rainbow babies and childrens hospital in 
cleveland has found that when the stroke is limited to one side of 
the brain these youngsters grow to have normal intelligence 
however they may have varying degrees of other problems including 
physical weakness on one side and trouble reading and talking 
