reopened a case involving people convicted of ira terrorism who 
claimed to be victims of a miscarriage of justice 
six irishmen serving life terms for pub bombings in birmingham in 
1974 that killed 21 people went before the court of appeal after a 
similar campaign but their convictions were upheld last year 
like the birmingham six the guildford four have figured strongly 
