<TEXT>
the soviet union announced agreements on 
tuesday with two us companies marriott corp and huntsman 
chemical corp to provide and package meals for passengers of the 
soviet airline aeroflot 
soviet ambassador yuri dubinin held a joint news conference with 
the heads of the two companies j w marriott jr of washington 
dc and jon huntsman of salt lake city to give details of the 
joint ventures set up without public announcement in moscow last 
month 
marriott said his company would spend 5 million on the venture 
which would include modernizing a threestory flight kitchen 
operation at moscows sheremetjevo airport 
he said he expects to use traditional soviet food but will also 
introduce more european and american cuisine on soviet flights he 
said it was the first time the soviets have arranged with a western 
company for contracted food services in the soviet union 
aeroflot already has contracts with marriott to provide meals on 
its airplanes at several airports outside the soviet union 
vladimar a nacharov aeroflot director general said soviet 
officials hope the new businesses will operate both efficiently 
and profitably he said the soviets made the deal with marriott 
because it was the only company with the capacity to serve the 
worlds largest airline which has flights to 3600 soviet and 100 
foreign airports and more than 180 million passengers a year 
asked if the soviet airline was currently serving meals on its 
flights nacharov said sometimes 
huntsman said the venture would mark the return of his company to 
food packaging after it sold off a company that designed mcdonalds 
hamburger containers 
his company in a separate joint agreement is to make plastic 
food services products for aeroflot with a manufacturing and 
packaging operation at the moscow airport 
marriott corp which says it provides over 150 million meals a 
year to 150 airlines said its moscow operation will be one of its 
biggest 
the joint sovietmarriott company is called aeromar ltd and is 
51 percent owned by aeroflot and 49 percent by marriott 
the operations are expected to begin this summer 
both marriott and huntsman said they were looking into other 
business ventures in the soviet union marriott said a team from his 
company would evaluate the feasibility of a moscow hotel huntsman 
said his company was evaluating a major petrochemical project in 
western siberia 
huntsman interviewed after the news conference said some 
eyebrows might be raised in utah over the fact that it took the 
soviet union to bring two mormon boys together in business 
though he and marriott who also has family roots in utah are 
longtime friends they have not taken part in such a business deal 
before 
