<TEXT>
former us sen gordon allott who 
during 18 years in the senate helped push through water projects 
instrumental to the economic development of colorado and arizona 
died of cancer tuesday he was 82 
allott died at swedish medical center where he was hospitalized 
dec 27 medical center spokeswoman beverly jacobsen said 
allott a republican held public office for much of his adult 
life culminating in his three terms in the us senate from 1955 to 
1973 he was thwarted in his bid for a fourth senate term by 
democrat floyd haskell in the 1972 general election allott lived in 
englewood in recent years 
born in pueblo on jan 2 1907 allott graduated from the 
university of colorado in boulder in 1927 and from its law school in 
1929 
in 1930 he moved to lamar where he practiced law and became 
prowers county attorney he also served terms as lamar city 
attorney district attorney and lieutenant governor from 195155 
when he also served as vice chairman of the state board of parole 
during world war ii allott was a major in the army air corps 
during his tenure in the senate allott served on the 
appropriations and interior committees he was the senate sponsor 
for the colorado river basin storage act of 1968 which provided for 
construction of five colorado water projects and the central arizona 
project the house sponsor was the late rep wayne aspinall a 
democrat with whom allott worked closely 
they got beat the same year 1972 at the start of the 
environmental age said former colorado gov john vanderhoof 
but thank god for them because they cinched the future for 
colorado 
allott is survived by his wife welda sons roger of aurora and 
gordon jr of littleton and three grandchildren 
a funeral was scheduled for 1 pm friday in denver 
</TEXT>
