industry watchers sales will remain sluggish in 1989 
rosalind wells chief economist of the national retail merchants 
association told storeowners monday that consumers are optimistic 
and confident about the economy but retail sales will increase only 
6 percent 275 percent after inflation 
americans have already put a lot of big purchases behind them 
and theres much less pentup demand she said 
ms wells and lyle gramley chief economist with the mortgage 
