citicorp the nations largest bank holding company and three 
other big banking concerns reported sharply higher earnings tuesday 
for both the fourthquarter of 1988 and the whole year 
most of the banks which included jp morgan amp co security 
pacific corp and wells fargo amp co said they were helped partly by 
tighter cost controls and brazils resumption of interest payments 
on foreign loans 
the earnings of all four banks were severely hurt in 1987 the 
peak of the third world debt crisis when brazil halted interest 
payments on bank loans and other economically troubled countries 
negotiated to restructure their debt citicorp said earnings for the 
three months ended dec 31 totaled 747 million or 219 a share 
compared with 621 million or 182 a share in the comparable 1987 
quarter 
for the year citicorps earnings totaled 185 billion or 536 
a share that compared with a loss of 118 billion in 1987 when 
the company decided to increase its provision to cover possible 
losses from shaky third world debt 
