1695 million or 146 a share vs a loss of 394 million the 
previous year 
its annual earnings reached 6389 million or 559 a share vs 
157 million or a penny a share in 1987 
wells fargo ranked 10th said fourth quarter earnings were 136 
million or 245 a share up 22 percent from 1112 million or 
196 a share in 1987 
for the year wells fargos earnings totaled 5125 million or 
920 vs 508 million or 52 cents in 1987 
citicorp said all sectors of the company did well partly due to 
tighter expense controls 
the company said quarterly and annual earnings included among 
other things 436 million from nearly two years of accumulated 
brazilian interest payments and 160 million from tax benefits 
stemming from its 3 billion addition in loanloss reserves in may 
1987 
jp morgan said it received 240 million of pastdue interest 
from brazil during the final quarter of 1988 on top of that its 
loanloss provision shrank to 200 million for all of 1988 from 
960 million in 1987 
